---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const jsonLd = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'TechArticle',
  headline: 'Provenant vs ScanCode — speed and output quality compared',
  description:
    'A reproducible, side-by-side comparison of Provenant and ScanCode on well-known repositories, covering both scan speed and the actual license and copyright findings that differ.',
  about: 'Open-source license and copyright scanning',
  url: 'https://getprovenant.github.io/compare/',
  isPartOf: { '@type': 'WebSite', name: 'Provenant', url: 'https://getprovenant.github.io/' },
};
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Provenant vs ScanCode — speed & output quality compared"
  description="A reproducible, side-by-side comparison of Provenant and ScanCode on well-known repositories: ~20× faster scans, plus an annotated look at the actual license and copyright findings that differ — and why."
  path="/compare/"
  ogType="article"
  ogImage="/assets/scan-duration-vs-files.svg"
  current="compare"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(jsonLd)} slot="head" />

  <main class="wrap">
    <section class="chero">
      <p class="eyebrow">Comparison · reproducible</p>
      <h1>Speed is easy to show. We measured quality too.</h1>
      <p class="sub">A faster scanner is only useful if it's still <em>right</em>. So we ran Provenant and ScanCode on the same well-known repositories, reduced both outputs to their actual findings, and compared them line by line — then annotated every difference that matters.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <div class="big-metrics">
        <div class="m"><div class="n tabnums">19.7<span class="u">×</span></div><div class="l">median speedup, 254 / 254 recorded runs</div></div>
        <div class="m"><div class="n tabnums">19.7<span class="u">×</span></div><div class="l">geometric-mean speedup overall</div></div>
        <div class="m"><div class="n tabnums">9→37<span class="u">×</span></div><div class="l">grows with size (sub-100 → 10k+ files)</div></div>
        <div class="m"><div class="n tabnums">70.7<span class="u">×</span></div><div class="l">fastest measured (CPython)</div></div>
      </div>

      <figure class="chart">
        <img src="/assets/scan-duration-vs-files.svg" alt="Log-log scatter of scan duration versus file count. Provenant's points sit consistently below ScanCode's across the full range, and the gap widens as file count grows." />
        <figcaption>Scan duration vs. file count, log-log. Provenant (lower is faster) stays below the reference across the whole range, and the gap widens with size.</figcaption>
      </figure>

      <div class="method">
        <b>How this was measured.</b> Both scanners run on identical checkouts at pinned commits, with the same scan profile, through Provenant's <code>compare-outputs</code> tool. It reduces each scan to normalized per-file findings, diffs them, and classifies every difference by direction. Speed figures are from <code>docs/BENCHMARKS.md</code>. The quality figures below come from a run on the current build (Provenant 0.2.8) at the commit noted, refreshed on each stable release.
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="repo">
      <h2>curl <span class="repo-mono">github.com/curl/curl</span></h2>
      <p class="tagline">The reference and Provenant agree on nearly every license conclusion. Where they diverge on copyright, Provenant is the more faithful of the two.</p>
      <div class="scorecard">
        <div class="s"><div class="sv tabnums">4,266</div><div class="sl">files compared</div></div>
        <div class="s"><div class="sv pv tabnums">99.9%</div><div class="sl">identical license detection (4,260 files)</div></div>
        <div class="s"><div class="sv tabnums">3 + 3</div><div class="sl">files where a detection differs (PV-only / SC-only)</div></div>
        <div class="s"><div class="sv pv tabnums">526</div><div class="sl">files where PV keeps the fuller copyright</div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="delta">
        <div class="dh"><span class="pill pill-teal">Copyright fidelity</span><h3>The same copyright — one scanner keeps all of it</h3></div>
        <div class="cmp"><span class="lbl sc">ScanCode</span><span class="val">Copyright (c) Daniel Stenberg, &lt;daniel@haxx.se&gt;</span><span class="ct">×800 files</span></div>
        <div class="cmp"><span class="lbl pv">Provenant</span><span class="val">Copyright (c) Daniel Stenberg, &lt;daniel@haxx.se&gt;<span class="keep">, et al.</span> <span class="keep">SPDX-License-Identifier: curl</span></span><span class="ct">×526 files</span></div>
        <div class="why">curl's file headers read <code>Copyright (C) Daniel Stenberg, &lt;daniel@haxx.se&gt;, et al.</code> followed by <code>SPDX-License-Identifier: curl</code>. ScanCode drops the <b>"et al."</b> — which legally signals that <b>other copyright holders exist</b> — and the SPDX identifier. Provenant reports the statement as written. It's the <b>same copyright</b>, rendered faithfully instead of trimmed.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="repro"><span class="k">repo</span> <span class="v">curl/curl @ 2bb5c9b</span> · <span class="k">profile</span> <span class="v">-clupe --system-package --strip-root</span> · <span class="k">provenant</span> <span class="v">0.2.8</span> · <span class="k">reference</span> <span class="v">ScanCode Toolkit</span> · <span class="k">refreshed at each stable release</span></div>
    </section>

    <section class="repo">
      <p style="color:var(--ink-soft)">This is one worked example from a much larger benchmark set. The full timing table across 254 recorded runs — with every commit pinned — lives in <a href="https://github.com/getprovenant/provenant/blob/main/docs/BENCHMARKS.md">docs/BENCHMARKS.md</a>, and every comparison here can be reproduced with the <code>compare-outputs</code> tool in the repository.</p>
      <div class="cta-row" style="margin-top:1.2rem">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="https://github.com/getprovenant/provenant#quick-start">Try Provenant</a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/blog/the-provenant-story/">Read the story →</a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <p class="legal">Provenant is an independent project, not affiliated with or endorsed by nexB Inc. or the AboutCode project. <span class="mono">ScanCode is a trademark of nexB Inc.</span> Comparative figures are drawn from reproducible scans on the commits noted above, for factual comparison.</p>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .chero { padding: clamp(2.6rem, 6vw, 4.5rem) 0 1.5rem; }
  .chero h1 { font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3.1rem); line-height: 1.05; margin: 0 0 1rem; font-weight: 660; }
  .chero .sub { font-size: clamp(1.05rem, 2.2vw, 1.25rem); color: var(--ink-soft); max-width: 42rem; margin: 0; text-wrap: pretty; }

  .big-metrics { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); gap: 1px; background: var(--border);
    border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: var(--radius); overflow: hidden; margin: 2.2rem 0; }
  .big-metrics .m { background: var(--surface); padding: 1.3rem 1.4rem; }
  .big-metrics .n { font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 2rem; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: -0.02em; color: var(--ink); }
  .big-metrics .n .u { color: var(--teal-ink); }
  .big-metrics .l { font-size: 0.82rem; color: var(--ink-faint); margin-top: 0.25rem; }
  @media (max-width: 480px) { .big-metrics { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }

  .chart { border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: var(--radius); background: var(--surface); padding: 1rem; margin: 1.5rem 0; }
  .chart img { display: block; width: 100%; height: auto; }
  .chart figcaption { font-size: 0.82rem; color: var(--ink-faint); font-family: var(--mono); margin-top: 0.6rem; }

  .method { background: var(--brass-soft); border: 1px solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--brass) 30%, transparent);
    border-radius: var(--radius); padding: 1.1rem 1.3rem; margin: 1.8rem 0; font-size: 0.93rem; color: var(--ink-soft); }
  .method b { color: var(--brass-ink); }

  .repo { padding: clamp(2.2rem, 5vw, 3.5rem) 0; border-top: 1px solid var(--border); }
  .repo h2 { font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 3.5vw, 2rem); margin: 0 0 0.3rem; font-weight: 640; }
  .repo h2 .repo-mono { font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 0.7em; color: var(--ink-faint); font-weight: 500; }
  .repo .tagline { color: var(--ink-soft); margin: 0 0 1.5rem; }

  .scorecard { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(9rem, 1fr)); gap: 1px; background: var(--border);
    border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: var(--radius); overflow: hidden; margin-bottom: 1.8rem; }
  .scorecard .s { background: var(--surface); padding: 0.95rem 1.1rem; }
  .scorecard .sv { font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 1.25rem; font-weight: 700; color: var(--ink); }
  .scorecard .sv.pv { color: var(--teal-ink); }
  .scorecard .sl { font-size: 0.76rem; color: var(--ink-faint); margin-top: 0.2rem; }

  .delta { border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: var(--radius); overflow: hidden; margin-bottom: 1.3rem; background: var(--surface); }
  .delta .dh { padding: 0.9rem 1.2rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 0.6rem; align-items: center; }
  .delta .dh h3 { font-size: 1.02rem; margin: 0; font-weight: 640; }
  .delta .cmp { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 5.5rem 1fr auto; gap: 0.5rem 1rem; align-items: baseline; padding: 0.85rem 1.2rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); }
  .delta .cmp .lbl { font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 0.78rem; padding-top: 0.15rem; }
  .delta .cmp .lbl.sc { color: var(--ref); }
  .delta .cmp .lbl.pv { color: var(--teal-ink); font-weight: 600; }
  .delta .cmp .val { font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 0.86rem; line-height: 1.5; word-break: break-word; color: var(--ink); }
  .delta .cmp .val .keep { color: var(--teal-ink); background: var(--teal-soft); border-radius: 3px; padding: 0 0.2em; }
  .delta .cmp .ct { font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 0.78rem; color: var(--ink-faint); white-space: nowrap; }
  .delta .why { padding: 0.85rem 1.2rem; background: var(--surface-2); font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--ink-soft); }
  .delta .why b { color: var(--ink); }

  .filelist { list-style: none; margin: 0; padding: 0.4rem 0; }
  .filelist li { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 0.5rem 0.9rem; align-items: baseline; padding: 0.5rem 1.2rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 0.83rem; }
  .filelist li:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
  .filelist .path { color: var(--ink); }
  .filelist .lic { color: var(--teal-ink); }
  .filelist .arrow { color: var(--ink-faint); }

  .repro { border: 1px dashed var(--border-strong); border-radius: var(--radius); padding: 1rem 1.2rem; margin-top: 1.4rem;
    font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 0.8rem; color: var(--ink-soft); line-height: 1.7; }
  .repro .k { color: var(--ink-faint); }
  .repro .v { color: var(--ink); }
</style>
